    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span>You are given an array with n elements.\nA given array is a special array if the absolute difference of consecutive elements is less than equal to 2.You have to find if on deleting any one element the resulting array can be  a special array.\n\n\n###Input:\n\n- The first line contains the number n which is the size of the array where $3 \\leq n \\leq 10000$ \n- The next n lines contain the numbers in the array which lie between [-100000,100000]\n\n###Output:\nIf the array can be converted into a special array print \u201cTrue\u201d.\nIf the array can\u2019t be converted into a special array print \u201cFalse\u201d\n\n\n###Sample Input:\n\t5\n\t1 2 6 4 6\n\n###Sample Output\n        True\n",
